Diagnosis . The most distinctive characters are: clypeus with one seta on each side anteriorly; pronotum with one lateral seta on each side and with basal angles blunt at apex; pronotal disc in central portion impunctate; elytra densely punctate and pubescent on all intervals, without row of discal pores on intervals 1, 3, 5 and 7 ; and legs reddish brown or brownish yellow. In addition, labial basal palpomere is not carinate, and median lobe of aedeagus (
Figs 15–16
) lacks any distinct sclerotized elements in the internal sac. Body length 8.3–12.5 mm .

Distribution . China : the north-western and eastern parts. It was reported from Xinjiang, Heilongjiang, Jilin, Liaoning, Shandong, Jiangsu, Gansu, Shanxi, Shaanxi, Hubei, Zhejiang, Yunnan (
Kataev et al . 2003
), Hebei (Schauberger 1938 ), Nei Mongol, Hubei, Henan, Anhui, Jiangxi, Sichuan, Guizhou, Fujian, Taiwan , Guangdong, Hunan, Guangxi, and Xizang (
Hua 2002
). We provided here the additional examined material from Xinjiang, Hebei, Sichuan and Guizhou.
